:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"layers updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2182\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:467:\"<p>The latest version of Layers is now live with a brand new Page Revisions feature that will give you piece of mind the next time you make any change to one of your Layers pages.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/\">Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here&#8217;s Why You Should Update</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"David Perel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4762:\"<h3>Introducing Page Revisions</h3>\n<p>Having piece of mind while you make changes to your site is important. There is nothing worse than accidentally deleting something you cannot recover and until today that was a scary possibility. We have been so focused on page revisions that we decided to release it before any other new 2016 features (more on that in a moment).</p>\n<p>So what do Page Revisions do? Well now every time you save a page, we will automatically store that as a version that you can revert back to at any point in the future. That means you can make as many changes as you like and should you not like them, you can roll back to a previous version with relative ease.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2193\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2193\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png\" alt=\"revisions-02\" width=\"1683\" height=\"880\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-300x157.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-768x402.png 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-1024x535.png 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png 1683w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1683px) 100vw, 1683px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In order to roll back all you need to do is go to the &#8220;Edit Page&#8221; section in WordPress, click on the specific page you want to revert and then click on &#8220;Revisions&#8221;. In there you&#8217;ll be presented with a timeline slider that will allow you to easily go back to a different state.</p>\n<p>The knock on affect of this change is equally important as we&#8217;re now storing your content in the same place that SEO plugins look. So from now on, Yoast, All in One SEO etc. are 100% compatible with Layers. It&#8217;s a big deal and one we&#8217;re quite proud of.</p>\n<h4>Some other important changes</h4>\n<p>Along with Page Revisions there have been some other changes on the admin site which you may find important:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>We&#8217;ve split out our admin CSS file into three separate files for easier management across different interfaces.</li>\n<li>The marketplace section has had a <em>complete redesign</em>, making it easier to browse and preview items.</li>\n<li>You can now select a primary color during the onboarding process. No more grey websites!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So don&#8217;t waste any time and update to Layers 1.2.11 directly from your WordPress dashboard</p>\n<h4>What&#8217;s Next?</h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2190\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2190\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png\" alt=\"new-link-interface-01\" width=\"660\" height=\"710\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1-279x300.png 279w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png 660w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With version 1.2.11 live we are already fully focused on the next release, here&#8217;s what you can look forward to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Smart/Dynamic linking &#8211; no more hard coding of page links! This will make it much easier to transfer a site from a dev environment to a live environment.</li>\n<li>Better onboarding &#8211; making Layers easier for new users is a pillar of the product so onboarding will be looked at in Feb.</li>\n<li>New preset page layouts &#8211; we want to expand our preset page layout options.</li>\n<li>New grid system &#8211; this isn&#8217;t guaranteed for the next release but is a huge focus for me (David) as we aim to make our grid layout more flexible.</li>\n<li>New HTML for SEO friendliness &#8211; this was planned for 1.2.11, but has been pushed out.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>One last thing!</h3>\n<p>February marks one year since Layers was <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/02/from-today-the-way-you-build-wordpress-sites-will-change-say-hello-to-layers/\">launched to the world</a>. Keep an eye out for our &#8216;bundle-a-week&#8217; special via our new newsletter called&#8230; &#8220;<a href=\"http://us10.campaign-archive1.com/?u=5b9a020fcf797987098cc7bca&amp;id=e7874277f7\">Not another Newsletter</a>&#8221; which is sent every week!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/\">Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here&#8217;s Why You Should Update</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"What’s In Store For Layers in early 2016\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 05 Jan 2016 13:09:11 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"layers updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2147\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:394:\"<p>The new year is already well underway at Layers HQ as we ramp up for an exciting 2016 with a packed development schedule focused on the Layers core.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/\">What&#8217;s In Store For Layers in early 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Vail Joy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3897:\"<p>We had such an overwhelmingly positive response to <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/\">Layers Pro</a> in the few short months it has been growing, and have several crazy-cool ideas for how to make it even more perfect. However, we know the furniture still gets wet if there is a hole in the roof and we want to ensure Layers is the best it can be, always. That&#8217;s why it will be receiving our full attention in the first quarter of 2016. Below is a peek at some of the things we will be looking at in-depth:</p>\n<h3>Onboarding</h3>\n<p>User friendliness is Layers primary feature. When you jump in for the first time, our setup wizard helps you along with basic configurations and video examples of using the customizer. Interface improvements, updated content and a variety of beautiful new presets are on the way to spice up the Layers Dashboard and onboarding process to delight you right into your next website project.</p>\n<h3>SEO</h3>\n<p>WordPress is already built to be extremely effective at SEO without much more effort than turning on permalinks, but when it comes to pages on your site, you&#8217;re at a disadvantage. Google already tends to rank your internal content higher when building search engine results due to its denser keywords &#8211; ignoring dynamic pages created from templates as those pages themselves actually contain no content and duplicate information from other pages on your site. This can make home page optimization tough!</p>\n<p>SEO is a top development priority for us in the coming months, and will include an overhaul of the HTML structure in the theme templates to ensure the HTML5 outline of your pages is optimal and up to 2016 standards.</p>\n<h3>Page Revisions</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_2152\" style=\"width: 1000px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2152\"><img class=\"wp-image-2152 size-full\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png\" alt=\"history-alpha\" width=\"990\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha-300x113.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha-768x290.png 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png 990w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 990px) 100vw, 990px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Alpha version of our new page history feature</p></div>\n<p>Using the revisions API you&#8217;ll soon be able to roll back to a previous version of your page should you not be happy with your changes or if your server experiences any unwanted issues. The aim here is piece of mind <img src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<h3>Performance</h3>\n<p>WordPress 4.4 <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/\" target=\"_blank\">introduced big improvements</a> to the Customizer in both use and performance, but with every big change always comes a little gremlin to make something else act out. We will be going in with flamethrowers in the coming weeks to flush out these annoyances and make the Layers customization experience smoother than ever before.</p>\n<p>Have Something You Want In Layers Not Listed Here?</p>\n<p>We love hearing from you on how you are using Layers and what features you would like to see and welcome you to submit feature requests on our <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/forums/\" target=\"_blank\">Layers Community site.</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/\">What&#8217;s In Store For Layers in early 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:109:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 10 Dec 2015 20:26:25 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"layers pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"themes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2107\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:421:\"<p>Overall the response to Layers Pro has been incredible so we wanted to keep the momentum and make it even better.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/\">Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"David Perel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7016:\"<h3>Let&#8217;s start with Layers Pro</h3>\n<p>Overall the response to Layers Pro has been incredible so we wanted to keep the momentum and make it even better.</p>\n<p>So with a big focus on serving you, our most valued users, we are happy to announce some big improvements:</p>\n<h4><strong>Background Videos</strong></h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/background-video.gif\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2119\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2119\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/background-video.gif\" alt=\"background-video\" width=\"640\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally Background videos are a possibility in Layers, allowing you to make bold visual statements when users enter your site.</p>\n<h4><strong>Social Widget</strong></h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2118\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2118\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png\" alt=\"social-icons-widget\" width=\"1100\" height=\"314\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-300x86.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-768x219.png 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-1024x292.png 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png 1100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This widget took much longer to developer than expected but it was for good reason. Our focus on UX is obsessive and we refused to release our Social Icon Widget until it was as intuitive as possible. We believe we have achieved that with global link inputs, widget and menu selection as well as the normal settings you&#8217;ve come to expect from Layers &#8211; including button coloring and sizing.</p>\n<h4><strong>Search in the Header</strong></h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2113\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2113 aligncenter\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg\" alt=\"search-pop-up\" width=\"1100\" height=\"790\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-300x215.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-768x552.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-1024x735.jpg 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-1000x720.jpg 1000w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg 1100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With Layers Pro you can now add a search button to the header of your site using a simple checkbox. When turned on, a search icon will appear inline with your menu and reveals a beautifully animated popup interface to search in.</p>\n<h4><strong>Header Background Image</strong></h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2111\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2111 aligncenter\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg\" alt=\"header-background\" width=\"1100\" height=\"488\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-300x133.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-768x341.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-1024x454.jpg 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg 1100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Layers Pro introduced deeper header customization and to make that even better we’re introducing header background image uploading.</p>\n<p>Last but not least we&#8217;ve added a <strong>Body Color Selector</strong> and improved <strong>Menu Styling</strong> which included hover states!</p>\n<p>If you don’t have Layers Pro yet, <a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/layers-pro-extended-customization-for-layers/11225042?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Layers%20Pro%201.2\">get it now for $25</a></p>\n<h3><b>StoreKit Updates</b></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2112\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2112 aligncenter\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg\" alt=\"header-cart-drop-down\" width=\"1100\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-300x164.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-768x419.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-1024x559.jpg 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg 1100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/storekit-woocommerce-for-layers/11223808?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20StoreKit%201.6\">StoreKit</a> has served as the backbone to the most valuable ecommerce functionality available for Layers. This week we’ve launched an update which adds a Header Mini Cart as well as new filters to the product widget including the ability to show only items on sale or only featured items.</p>\n<h3><b>Two new themes</b></h3>\n<p>If that wasn’t enough we also focused on getting two new themes out the gates before the end of 2015. They’re called Acquire 2.0 and Concept Living…</p>\n<p>Concept Living, announced a few weeks ago, is part of a strategy to bring some of our best selling themes onto the Layers platform &#8211; find out more about the <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living\">Furniture theme</a> here.</p>\n<p>Acquire 2.0 is a big update of one of the first ever Layers themes. We decided to give it a more comprehensive design along with more page templates to choose from. Check out the demo or go directly to the <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/acquire-wordpress-corporate-theme/11220959?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Acquire%202.0\">business theme</a> to find out more.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/\">Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"What’s in Layers 1.2.10\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 08 Dec 2015 14:49:49 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2083\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:504:\"<p>You ask, we listen.  Layers 1.2.10 out and includes several fixes and code improvements to make the new WordPress 4.4 update even better. We also have a ton of Layers improvements coming your way for the holidays, plus some huge additions to our Extensions that are sure to make you smile.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/\">What&#8217;s in Layers 1.2.10</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Vail Joy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3148:\"<p>Before jumping into updating Layers, be sure to update your Layers Updater plugin to version 1.2. You can find this updated version under Layers &gt; Dashboard. See <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/update-layers/\" target=\"_blank\">this doc for or step-by-step instructions on updating your plugin</a>.</p>\n<h3>Fixed Transparent Headers Are Back</h3>\n<p>We made several changes in 1.2.8 to where options are placed in the Customizer to make finding them easier. One of these changes included a slick little toggle for the Sticky Header that basically hid the Transparency option unless you turned Sticky on. We realize now that was confusing for some people, so these two options are no longer dependent on one another.</p>\n<p>Layers Pro users who have access to the Blog customizer will also find their sidebar layout options inside the related Posts &amp; Pages section rather than up under Site Settings.</p>\n<h3>Video Backgrounds</h3>\n<p>A few years ago, when we first introduced video backgrounds into our Obox Slider, we had no idea how popular it would really be. Video use in web design was just beginning to trend and we weren&#8217;t sure if the average person would have any idea how to take advantage of them.</p>\n<p>Since then video backgrounds have exploded across the web and proved a big success in terms of added functionality. We felt Layers needed this in the core, too, and so the Layers Slider Widget will now support embedded video from Vimeo, YouTube or a self-hosted .mp4 when the <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/\">Layers Pro</a> extension is active. This feature, along with several more goodies, are coming later this week with Layers Pro 1.2, so keep an eye on this space or <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Oboxthemes\" target=\"_blank\">our Twitter feed</a> for the announcement.</p>\n<p>For designers, this means you no longer need to resort to using a different slider plugin to get full motion graphics into your slider. For developers, this means even better controls for adding your own options to the core widgets to expand their functionality in your own themes and extensions.</p>\n<h3>Bug Fixes</h3>\n<p>Layers 1.2.10 fixes several niggles, including a missing round image ratio in the Posts widget, Boxed slider alignment issues, and a missing content container in archives with no content. We naturally aim to have Layers be 100% bug free one day, but to make that happen we need your help.</p>\n<p>To get help with Layers issues or report a possible bug, and to contribute your ideas and code to the project, be sure to visit our <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com\" target=\"_blank\">Community Forums</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/Obox/layerswp\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub project</a>.</p>\n<p>To learn more about the technical additions to this update, or for help with updating, visit the <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/layers-release-1-2-10/\" target=\"_blank\">1.2.10 update page</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/\">What&#8217;s in Layers 1.2.10</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"Get Excited for Faster Layers Customization in WordPress 4.4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 30 Nov 2015 15:26:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2054\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:483:\"<p>WordPress 4.4 is due for release on December 8th, bringing a host of front-end improvements and developer love. See what goodies are in store for Layers and how this is the best WordPress update yet!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/\">Get Excited for Faster Layers Customization in WordPress 4.4</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Vail Joy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4673:\"<p>WordPress 4.4 is due for release on December 8th (hopefully there are no delays like last time), bringing a host of front-end improvements and developer love. We are especially excited for this release as it means even more improvements to Customizer performance and responsive image handling.</p>\n<p>Version 4.4 also means the full implementation of the REST API, making it even easier to include common libraries like Ajax in your plugins. For more on that specifically, see the <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/10/28/rest-api-welcome-the-infrastructure-to-core/\" target=\"_blank\">introductory post over on Make WordPress Core</a>.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at the most exciting improvements coming in this release:</p>\n<h4>Performance Improvements</h4>\n<p>As <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/10/what-the-new-wordpress-customizer-roadmap-means-for-layers/\" target=\"_blank\">previously reported</a>, WordPress 4.4 promises the first of the Customizer Roadmap for improving performance and functionality of site customization. How this translates to you and your Layers site is that<span class=\"s1\"> widgets are no longer all loaded at once, creating a massive performance slump as the Customizer interface is loaded.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"s1\">Instead, each Widget gets initialized only when it is needed.  This leads to a more snappy interface when changing and updating your widgets in the Customizer, and a far quicker initial load of the interface.</span></p>\n<h4>Responsive Images</h4>\n<p>As of today, the average web page <a href=\"http://httparchive.org/interesting.php?a=All&amp;l=Sep%2015%202015#bytesperpage\">currently weighs over 2 MB</a> with the majority of those bytes being attributed to images. Rapidly evolving browser, screen size and resolution support across mobile devices also means site owners are having to include more and more image versions, sizes or formats.</p>\n<p>WordPress saw the opportunity to make a huge impact on the web &#8211; seeing as how it runs more than 25% of all websites &#8211; by adding responsive image support out of the box so sites can serve appropriate sizes images to all users.</p>\n<p>If you are a child theme developer, you can take advantage of these changes through wp_get_attachment_image_srcset and the srcset attribute in the image tag. An example of the implementation can be found on the WordPress <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/09/30/responsive-images-merge-proposal/\" target=\"_blank\">developer blog</a>.</p>\n<h4>Your Content is Now Embeddable</h4>\n<p>WordPress has allowed you to easily embed content from oEmbed providers such as YouTube and SoundCloud by adding share links to your post content or widgets, and with 4.4 your WordPress site is now its own <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/10/28/new-embeds-feature-in-wordpress-4-4/\" target=\"_blank\">oEmbed provider</a>! This means others can embed your content the same way and have it automatically appear in a neat oEmbed format.</p>\n<p>Using a handful of filters, you can customize how your site looks when it’s embedded elsewhere. As a part of the work around embeds, there are also a couple of new functions for retrieving and displaying embeddable content. The post above also links to a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/disable-embeds/\">plugin</a> which will remove the ability to embed your site elsewhere.</p>\n<h4>Updating WordPress</h4>\n<p>If you develop child themes or extensions, or just want to check out the new 4.4 features before it hits on the 8th,  you can grab the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-beta-tester/\">WordPress beta Tester</a> plugin to easily sync to the latest build. Of course, we don&#8217;t recommend you install WordPress 4.4 on a live website before it is actually released.</p>\n<p>You should begin seeing the update notifications hit your WordPress admin, beginning next Tuesday, with a possible week delay if you have a Managed WordPress solution that updates it for you.</p>\n<p>For more information about WordPress 4.4 and an overview of the REST API and other developer goodies, head over to the <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/11/11/wordpress-4-4-field-guide/\">WordPress 4.4 Field Guide</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>What are you looking forward to in future versions of WordPress? Let us know in the comments below.</strong></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/\">Get Excited for Faster Layers Customization in WordPress 4.4</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Easy WordPress White-labeling For Your Clients\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 24 Oct 2015 12:46:10 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"brand wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"white label\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=1775\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:471:\"<p>We discuss all the ways you can white-label your client site through things as simple as turning off the Layers link in the footer, to which plugins allow for the easiest logo replacement and admin customization.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/\">Easy WordPress White-labeling For Your Clients</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Vail Joy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12709:\"<p>If you design or setup websites for clients, you know how important it is to offer a smooth and branded, yet client-proof administration experience. White-labeling is a term that describes re-branding or removing 3rd party branding from your website&#8217;s front and back-end. Doing so increases brand recognition for your design company or service.</p>\n<p>While it is not possible to completely re-brand a WordPress site without extensive customization, you can white-label or brand the most essential and visible aspects of the WordPress Admin interface without having to resort to custom Admin themes or other coding hacks.</p>\n<p>You can take white-labeling one step further and also customize certain aspects of the WordPress Admin through menu tools and role editors to simplify its use and keep your clients from dangerous options such as updates or code editors.</p>\n<p>If you are building a child theme or custom plugin for your site and prefer to implement as much admin customization as you can via functions, see our <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/how-to-white-label-the-wordpress-admin/\" target=\"_blank\">Dev Tutorial for How to White Label the WordPress Admin</a></p>\n<h3>Disabling Layers Footer Icon</h3>\n<p>Layers will add a small Layers badge to the footer of your site by default which you can disable from the Customizer under the Footer Styling panel. Of course, you get extra-awesome points for leaving it on and helping spread the word about the Layers framework.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2039\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/support-layers.jpg\" alt=\"support-layers\" width=\"288\" height=\"86\" /></p>\n<h3>Adding Your Own Credit &amp; Copyright Text</h3>\n<p>The text footer of Layers contains a default copyright that you may customize from the Customizer under the Footer Styling panel. This field also accepts basic HTML, so adding an icon or logo of your own is as simple as grabbing the file url to your image in the Media Library, and linking it from a standard <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag.</p>\n<p>See <a class=\"question-title\" href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-add-images-to-the-footer/\" rel=\"bookmark\">How to Add Images to the Footer Copyright area</a> for a detailed tutorial on adding images in the Layers footer.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2040\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/copyrighttext.jpg\" alt=\"copyrighttext\" width=\"288\" height=\"86\" /></p>\n<h3>Replacing WordPress Login and Admin Logos</h3>\n<p>If your clients or staff are logging in through the traditional WordPress admin page, they will be greeted by a WordPress logo that links to the site main page. This can be confusing for less-savvy users, especially if they click that logo and are whisked away from the login without knowing quite what happened.</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2041 alignright\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/wp-login.jpg\" alt=\"wp-login\" width=\"344\" height=\"469\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/wp-login-220x300.jpg 220w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/wp-login.jpg 344w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 344px) 100vw, 344px\" /></p>\n<p>You can change this logo with custom functions in a child theme, or using a plugin such as <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ag-custom-admin/\" target=\"_blank\">AG Custom Admin</a>. This free plugin is an essential part of any site you build and plan to maintain for your clients.</p>\n<p>It allows you to customize all the branded aspects of the WordPress admin, including logos and admin footer text.</p>\n<p>By giving your clients the role of Editor (rather than Administrator), you can also  lock down important menu links and add new ones, which we will expand on in a bit.</p>\n<p>With AG Custom Admin enabled, click on Tools AG Custom Admin to access the Admin Bar and Login Page tabs for logo and color customization. Be careful with the first three options to disable the admin bar or admin bar customizations.</p>\n<p>If you want your clients to be able to create and edit Layers pages, you should allow them to retain access to the admin bar while viewing the front-end so they can easily click into the Customizer from any page.</p>\n<h3>Change WordPress Admin Bar</h3>\n<p>Once logged in, your client is going to see the WordPress Dashboard with the default Howdy! greeting and a WordPress branded admin bar. If you&#8217;ve decided to go the easy route with AG Custom Admin, you can change the Admin branding options on the Admin tab:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload your logo to the WordPress Media Library</li>\n<li>Grab the File Url from the right side of the Image details screen once it is uploaded</li>\n<li>In the AG Custom Admin options, paste the URL into the Change Admin Bar Logo field. You may also simply hide the icon by checking the Hide WordPress Logo option below this.</li>\n<li>Scroll to the bottom to find the Change Howdy text and Change Logout Text to customize these messages.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Change Admin Colors</h3>\n<p>The AG Custom Admin plugin  offers a Colorizer tab for changing the admin menu and admin bar colors.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2043\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/custom-admin.jpg\" alt=\"custom-admin\" width=\"852\" height=\"608\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/custom-admin-300x214.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/custom-admin.jpg 852w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 852px) 100vw, 852px\" /></p>\n<p>To do this on your own with a child theme, you would need to write a custom admin.css file, then enqueue it normally from your Child Theme functions:</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function layers_child_admin_css() {\r\n    wp_enqueue_style( \r\n      \'admin_css\', \r\n      get_stylesheet_directory_uri() . \'/assets/css/admin.css\' );\r\n}\r\n\r\nadd_action(\'admin_enqueue_scripts\', \'layers_child_admin_css\' );</pre><p>You can also write the CSS directly to the function and have it output in the admin head:</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function my_custom_admin_style() { \r\n   echo \'&lt;style&gt; body, td, textarea, input, select { \r\n      font-family: \"Lucida Grande\"; \r\n      font-size: 12px; \r\n   } &lt;/style&gt;\'; \r\n}\r\n\r\nadd_action(\'admin_head\', \'my_custom_admin_style\');</pre><p>For a detailed walkthrough on building admin CSS, see <a href=\"http://code.tutsplus.com/articles/customizing-the-wordpress-admin-adding-styling--wp-33530\" target=\"_blank\">Customizing the WordPress Admin by our friends at Tuts+</a></p>\n<h3>Change the WordPress Admin Footer</h3>\n<p>At the bottom of every page in the WordPress admin you will find a Thank You for Creating with WordPress! message and a version number. If your clients don&#8217;t know or care that you are using WordPress for the site, or if you just want more control over outgoing links and branding, you can change or remove this easily.</p>\n<p>From AG Custom Admin options, head into the Admin Footer tab where you can find the Change Footer Text and Change Footer Version fields, or options to hide them.</p>\n<h3>Customizing the Admin Dashboard</h3>\n<p>Now that you have customized the visual aspects of the WordPress Admin, you can start thinking about the content you want your clients and site users to see. The WordPress Dashboard is the first content a logged in user sees, and while anyone can customize their own view via the Screen Options menu, you may need to remove existing metaboxes, or add some new ones to deliver the best user experience for your client.</p>\n<p>The next tab in your AG Custom Admin options is the Admin Dashboard tab. Here you can easily add content and HTML to the Dashboard header, and disable any default widgets. What this does not do is allow you to turn off widgets added through other plugins or by Layers. To do that, you will need to reference the plugin options or add a custom function to a child theme.</p>\n<h3>Customizing the Admin Menu &amp; Client Access</h3>\n<p>In most cases where you are maintaining your client websites, it is a good idea to restrict access to certain admin areas, both for the safety of the site overall, and simply to reduce confusion for clients unfamiliar with the WordPress Admin. Examples might be hiding links to plugin settings (such as AG Custom Admin), the Appearance &gt; Editor screen or Layers Marketplace.</p>\n<p>Customizing the Admin menu is a task truly best left to a plugin. Both AG Custom Admin and specialized plugins like <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/admin-menu-editor/\" target=\"_blank\">Admin Menu Editor</a> are actively developed and updated, and can get the job done for free.</p>\n<p>If using AG Custom Admin, you may edit all admin menu labels and access rights from the Admin Menu tab of the settings. Checking a menu item will remove it from access for Editors, so this plugin depends on you ensuring your clients User Role is set to Editor and not Administrator.</p>\n<p>If your client is the type that likes to see the Admin role on their account, but is too dangerous to be left with full rights, you can use another very handy free plugin called <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/members/\" target=\"_blank\">Members</a>, written by WordPress Core developer Justin Tadlock. This is the best approach if you choose to move forward with using the Admin Menu Editor plugin instead, and here&#8217;s why.</p>\n<h4>Creating a Super User and Editing Client Privileges</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>With the Members plugin active, go to Users &gt; Roles.</li>\n<li>Click Add New to add a new role called &#8220;Super-Admin.&#8221;</li>\n<li>Check the boxes on all the capabilities and Save</li>\n<li>Now back out to the main Users list and edit yourself. Select the new Super Admin role from the Role drop-down and Save.</li>\n<li>Return to the Users &gt; Roles page and edit Administrator. Here is where you can remove some capabilities from this role. Common capabilities you want to Deny would be:\n<ul>\n<li>General: edit_roles: deny ability to change your custom roles</li>\n<li>Appearance: switch_themes: deny ability to switch themes from your set active theme.</li>\n<li>Plugins: activate_plugins: deny ability to install new plugins that may potentially break the site.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The important step here is that your clients are assigned the Admin role while you have Super Admin with all capabilities. When using Admin Menu Editor for example, you can now turn off specific Admin Menu items or sub-links by setting them to the Super Admin role.</p>\n<p>This is useful for hiding menu links such as Marketplace, Tools, Editor and other plugin items you might have such as Performance or SEO. You can also hide the entire Layers menu from your clients if you wish.</p>\n<p>With both AG Custom Admin and Admin Menu Editor, you may also customize menu icons and labels and rearrange them with drag and drop if needed.</p>\n<h3>Adding Links To the Admin Menu</h3>\n<p>Easily add new links or entire Admin Menus from the Admin Menu tab of AG Custom Admin (bottom of page) or using the Add Menu button in the Admin Menu Editor options. This allows you to build helpful menus that link to most-used admin pages or offsite resources.</p>\n<h3>Creating Custom Onboarding Pages</h3>\n<p>If you have developed a Layers Child Theme for your client project or are thinking about using one instead of plugins, you can add a custom onboarding function that displays the first time your client logs in with your child theme active, or which they can revisit from a custom menu option.</p>\n<p>We wrote a full developer article on how to do this in a Layers Child Theme as part of the Child Theme Author Guide: <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/how-to-add-help-pages-onboarding-to-layers-themes-or-extensions/\">How to Add Help Pages &amp; Onboarding to Layers Themes or Extensions</a></p>\n<h3>Changing Text in Layers</h3>\n<p>In extreme cases where you need to remove Layers branding, you must use a translation tool to remove each instance of &#8220;Layers.&#8221; See our <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-translate-or-localize-layers/\" target=\"_blank\">guide on translating Layers </a>for plugin suggestions and tips.</p>\n<p>Know of some other great plugins or ways to customize the WordPress Admin that we didn&#8217;t cover here? Tell us in the comments!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/\">Easy WordPress White-labeling For Your Clients</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"Refreshing a best seller with Concept Living, a WordPress Furniture Theme\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 10:30:55 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"themes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2016\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:417:\"<p>We’re on a mission to bring some of our finest Obox Themes into the Layers fold. Step 1 in that process is Concept Living.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/\">Refreshing a best seller with Concept Living, a WordPress Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Marc Perel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2297:\"<p>Today we’re happy to launch <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living%20Launch%20Post\">Concept Living</a>, a WordPress furniture theme for furniture retailers. Originally called Store and built on Obox Themes technology, we decided that Layers offered a perfect opportunity to modernize it.</p>\n<p>During Obox Themes’ 7 year existence we have created well over 100 themes, some for WordPress, some for Tumblr, some for Posterous… but mostly WordPress.</p>\n<p>Of those themes there have been some stand out performers, including <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/gigawatt-wordpress-video-theme/492944?ref=obox\">Gigawatt</a>, <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/retail-therapy-multipurpose-ecommerce-theme/5636873?ref=obox\">Retail Therapy</a>, <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/the-writer-premium-wordpress-blogging-theme/5908925?ref=obox\">The Writer</a> etc. So when we sat down to decide what our next Layers theme was going to be we realized that the answer may be staring us in the face &#8211; why not take our best Obox Themes and give them a fresh coat of paint and a brand new foundation?</p>\n<p>New features include a mobile first design, multiple header layouts, StoreKit integration, Layers page building functionality and much more.</p>\n<p>Check out the <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/full_screen_preview/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living%20Launch%20Post\">demo</a> or find out more by visiting <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living%20Launch%20Post\">Concept Living</a> on Themeforest.</p>\n<p>We look forward to bringing you much more of our finest work in the near future.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/\">Refreshing a best seller with Concept Living, a WordPress Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"Introducing Layers Pro, the best extension we’ve ever made\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 18 Nov 2015 08:45:45 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Layers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"layers updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2001\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:380:\"<p>Unlock customizability in the Layers framework with extended control over design and layout settings.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/\">Introducing Layers Pro, the best extension we’ve ever made</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Marc Perel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4851:\"<p>The number one request we get from Layers users is the ability to do more. More customizability, more colors, more control.</p>\n<p>When we set about building Layers we wanted to focus on the most important needs of a website and then work our way up from there. Our number one focus was to avoid throwing the kitchen sink at you.</p>\n<p>The strategy has worked well, with tons of great sites being built, but as people have conquered the logic of page building so they have reached a point where more control is needed.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/\">Layers Pro</a> bridges the gap between a solid site and being really creative.</p>\n<h3><b>What does Layers Pro give me?</b></h3>\n<p>There are a number of features that Layers Pro enables when you install the extension on your site:</p>\n<h4><b>Header Styling</b></h4>\n<p>Finally you can “make the logo bigger” with flexible logo size options, and if our small, medium, large and massive  presets aren’t perfect for you then we’ve included ‘custom’ resizing too.</p>\n<p>Height adjustment and menu spacing has been included for that pixel perfect header layout.</p>\n<p>Another big request was the ability to customize your site menus, which is now possible with colors, spacing, shadows and text-transforming.</p>\n<h4><b>Blog Controls</b></h4>\n<p>From day one you can determine exactly which elements you’d like to display on your list and post pages:</p>\n<p><strong>These include the toggling of:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Featured Images</li>\n<li>Post Dates</li>\n<li>Post Categories</li>\n<li>Post Tags</li>\n<li>Post Author</li>\n<li>Post Excerpt lengths and the “Read More” button text can be changed too.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4><b>More Color Options</b></h4>\n<p>You requested deeper color customization, so we went to town…</p>\n<p>Color options are now split into contextual areas which cuts out the need to click in and out of accordions to get to the place you want. It’s a massive UX improvement that’s performed well in testing.</p>\n<p>Button customization is also vastly improved with the addition of border color, thickness and radius. You can determine button styling on both light and dark backgrounds.</p>\n<p>Menu coloring, blog post coloring, widgets and more have been included in <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/\">Layers Pro</a>.</p>\n<p>We will constantly be adding new color customization parameters to Layers Pro so that you have even more control over your site without requiring knowledge of code.</p>\n<h4><b>Tweak the Footer</b></h4>\n<p>New footer options have been added with the inclusion of a new height setting and color customization.</p>\n<h4><b>4 New Widgets and a great update to the Content Widget</b></h4>\n<p>A major part of <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/\">Layers Pro</a> is the inclusion of new widgets which allow for different ways to display content:</p>\n<p>The <strong>Tab</strong> and <strong>Accordion</strong> widgets enable you to present multiple pages or paragraphs of content in one place. Use it for sequential information such as steps or product tours, or group information that relates to each other.</p>\n<p>We’ve included a new <strong>Post Carousel</strong> widget which outputs your latest blog posts and can slide via controls or automatically with a timer of your choice.</p>\n<p>A much needed <strong>Call to Action</strong> widget is also available from today which you can use to direct user to your products, important blog posts or contact page with multiple buttons under a big header, you no longer have to use the Slider Widget. With the ability to include multiple buttons you can invite them to try your product or read more about it. The choice is yours.</p>\n<p>The most powerful widget, the Content Widget, has also received a subtle but important update which now allows you to add custom class name to individual columns. This will give CSS developers much more flexibility when customizing client or personal websites.</p>\n<h4><b>This is just the start</b></h4>\n<p>We want to ensure that Layers Pro takes the free version of Layers and turns it up to 11. The features we’ve announced today are just the first step in what we hope will be a long update cycle with more features added every month. So if you have any special requests let us know!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/\">Find out more about Layers Pro</a> or go to directly to CodeCanyon and <a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/layers-pro-extended-customization-for-layers/11225042?ref=obox\">purchase it</a> right away.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/\">Introducing Layers Pro, the best extension we’ve ever made</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"14\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"How to Speed Up Your WordPress Website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/how-to-speed-up-your-website/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/how-to-speed-up-your-website/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 07 Nov 2015 13:45:06 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=1794\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:402:\"<p>One of the most critical ingredients in your website\'s success recipe is its performance, in this post we give you some tips on how to improve your WordPress site speed.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/how-to-speed-up-your-website/\">How to Speed Up Your WordPress Website</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Vail Joy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15403:\"<p>Performance is based on several factors such as interface usability, load times and mobile compatibility, but the load time is where things usually go quickly downhill.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts.png\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1989 size-full\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"990\" height=\"914\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts-300x277.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts.png 990w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 990px) 100vw, 990px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It is surprisingly easy to end up with a sluggish WordPress website, no matter how minimal you may have set out to make it. Little things from your web host choice all the way to your WordPress configuration can lead to slow loading times for visitors, and according to Kissmetrics, nearly 40% of people will surf somewhere else if the page takes more than a few seconds to display anything.</p>\n<p>Slow performance is especially problematic for online stores, where you may have several visitors performing complex actions on your site at a single time.  A majority of shoppers were found in this study to be less likely to buy from a site that is slow or displaying other problems that keep them from having a smooth experience.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts-02.png\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1990 size-full\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts-02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"990\" height=\"1229\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts-02-242x300.png 242w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts-02-825x1024.png 825w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/every-second-counts-02.png 990w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 990px) 100vw, 990px\" /></a></p>\n<p>While 30% are pretty patient, willing to wait 6-10 seconds for a page load, you want to aim for less than that. Most sites running WordPress can load between 1-3 seconds.</p>\n<p>Here are a few effective tips for troubleshooting slow performance in the front-end of your site, and getting it running quickly and efficiently.</p>\n<h3>Why Your Site is Slow</h3>\n<p>The first step to troubleshooting a slow site or preparing a new one for snappy performance is understanding where slow-downs originate. The most common cause of slow page loads is slow internet speed, which is nothing you can control, but there are a number of things to check in your WordPress setup.</p>\n<p>Things that can aggravate site load times in a site using Layers are:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Cheap (slow) web hosting</li>\n<li>Low database memory allocation on your server</li>\n<li>Too many plugins activated</li>\n<li>Large file size of content such as HD images</li>\n<li>Script conflicts between plugins or large numbers of errors being generated</li>\n<li>3rd Party content including videos, hosted files or banner ads that take too long to connect to the host</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Your theme choice can be a factor in load speed as well. Some themes package a colossal amount of scripting, animations and other libraries that load on ever page.</p>\n<p>Layers is specifically designed to avoid this kind of &#8220;bloat factor&#8221; by building out functionality already present in the WordPress core, the aim of which is a minimal load.</p>\n<p>We also <a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/07/how-to-speed-up-the-wordpress-customizer/\" target=\"_blank\">do regular speed optimizations inside and out</a> to stay on top of performance considerations within the limitations of what we can do from a theme development standpoint.</p>\n<h3>What You Can Do</h3>\n<p>When testing your site, use a demo URL like <a href=\"http://tools.pingdom.com/fpt/#!/eAiQ2E/http://vailjoy.com/layers/\" target=\"_blank\">this one</a> as a benchmark. This demo is installed on WordPress Hosting at BlueHost does not have any caching enabled, and receives only medium traffic.</p>\n<p>By comparison, <a href=\"http://tools.pingdom.com/fpt/#!/ehYIpw/http://layerswp.com\" target=\"_blank\">this site</a>, also running Layers, has a <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/reference/child-theme/\" target=\"_blank\">child theme</a> and several plugins, runs on a WordPress multi-site on a different host, and receives high traffic. Both load in under 2 seconds.</p>\n<p>While the theme files themselves won&#8217;t cause slowdowns, certain <em>functionality</em> in your theme may support <strong>content</strong> that causes slowdowns. The fix typically depends on your setup. Here are some things you can do to troubleshoot:</p>\n<h4>Evaluate Internet Speed</h4>\n<p>Sometimes slow loading is just your connection being slow, or your host being slow. The best test is to ask someone in a different location to try visiting your URL and see how their experience compares.</p>\n<p>Your host can also test the load and explain any limitations of your hosting. If you have a large photography website, or an eCommerce site with a lot of traffic for example, you may need to upgrade to a VPS or WordPress hosting tier to avoid your traffic being throttled.</p>\n<h4>Run an Initial Speed Test</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://tools.pingdom.com/fpt/\">Pingdom</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/speed/pagespeed/\">Google Pagespeed</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Both of these resources will scan your site for specific load inhibitors and produce a report. Keep in mind that it is going to advise you about all inhibitors, whether they are a real problem or not.</p>\n<p>On Pingdom, all resources in your homepage will be listed. Typically the theme sylesheets load first, followed by plugins and scripting, and finally, the assets on the page, such as images, will load last and typically take the longest.</p>\n<p>Pay special attention to the very first ping, which is how long it takes the browser to communicate with the server and receive a response from your domain. Long load times here indicate a DNS or server issue, so it may be worth running a “DNS Health” test on your main website URL.</p>\n<p>For Google Pagespeed, ensure you are looking at the <strong>Desktop</strong> diagnostics tab. Items in the Red section of Pagespeed are the things to watch out for.  If you are not familiar with the terminology used, below is a brief outline of what some of the results mean and what you should do about them or not:</p>\n<h4>Optimize Images</h4>\n<p>If you have a significant amount of graphics or images on your site, they can cause a lot of load time if they are not as small in file size as possible. In many cases, the savings are marginal and not necessary, but if you see the size reduction is more than a few hundred kb, you probably need to re-process and re-upload your images (details in the next section)</p>\n<h4>Reduce Server Response Time</h4>\n<p>Cheap hosting often means slow speeds, and can be made worse by other sites on the same host taking up too much bandwidth or database memory. Contact your host if this is brought up as an issue.</p>\n<h4>Reduce Content Loading Before the Fold (aka render-blocking content)</h4>\n<p>This is a pretty idealistic option and one you can’t do much to directly influence, as WordPress sites need to load a measure of data, scripting or stylesheets at the beginning of the page.</p>\n<p>Layers is specifically optimized for load, and will not load anything at the beginning that is not explicitly required to load that way.</p>\n<p>Your plugins and <a href=\"http://kb.oboxthemes.com/glossary/page-template/\">page templates</a> will also dynamically load in scripts or styles being used on that page, and it all happens in the header. In most cases, this is not the cause of your site being slow, but can be if the page is looking for offsite content.</p>\n<h4>Reduce Offsite Content</h4>\n<p>This refers to functionality or content in your site that comes from somewhere else, including Google Fonts, Twitter or Facebook widgets, sharing buttons, or hosted scripts like Google Analytics, Vimeo videos, hotlinked images and so on.</p>\n<p>If these sites are experiencing downtime or slowdowns, your site will be forced to wait until a timeout limit is exceeded and an error is produced or the page skips the element and keeps loading. This should not deter you from using these services, but is important to be aware of the potential impacts.</p>\n<h4>Check Your Content</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>If you have a theme with a lot of <strong>video content </strong>that uses the Layers video embed url field in posts, ensure the <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/reference/oembed/\">oEmbed</a> url starts with //: or http:// and not https://</li>\n<li>For sites with a lot of <strong>images</strong>, ensure images are optimized for the web by saving them as JPGs, scaling them down to no larger than 2000px wide or less than 2MB in file size.\n<ul>\n<li>See <a href=\"http://kb.oboxthemes.com/articles/how-to-prepare-photos-for-your-website/\">How to Prepare Photos for Your Website</a></li>\n<li>Download and run the <strong>Regenerate Thumbnails</strong> or <strong>WPSmush It</strong> plugin</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Do not hotlink images. In other words, ensure all images on your site are hosted on your site and not from a 3rd party website, flickr, instagram or similar. These options are great for creating galleries using thumbnails and so on, but if these sites timeout on loading large images, your site will be slow.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Verify Plugin Compatibility</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Temporarily deactivate all plugins<strong> </strong>(excluding WooCommerce), then clear your browser cache and test the load again. If it is improved, you will need to reactivate plugins one at a time to figure out if there is a conflict, or reduce the number of plugins you have activated.</li>\n<li>Use as few plugins for front-end stuff as possible. Most hosts only allow between 32 and 64M of database memory for shared hosting, which can be quickly exceeded on sites running a ton of plugins. Evaluate how important a plugin is to your site and decide if it can be removed or consolidate by finding plugins that do more than one thing.</li>\n<li>Always use plugins that are actively developed or supported by their author, are cleared for use on the current WordpPress version, and have a decent rating (make sure 5 star plugins have several hundred votes, not just a handful, which can be very misleading!)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you are using WordPress SEO by Yoast, go to <strong><span class=\"admin-menu-item\">SEO</span></strong> &gt; <strong><span class=\"admin-menu-item\">TITLES</span> </strong>and uncheck the <em>Force Rewrite Titles</em> option. You can check the <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/support/plugin/wordpress-seo\" target=\"_blank\">plugin’s support forums</a> for examples of others affected by slowdowns and some possible solutions. If you find this helped, see the following for advice on optimizing settings.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>If you are using <strong>WP Super Cache</strong>, clear it, deactivate it, and replace it with a plugin that is known for less problems such as Quick Cache</li>\n<li>If you are using <strong>W3 Total Cache</strong>, go to <span class=\"admin-menu-item\"><strong>PERFORMANCE</strong> </span>&gt; <span class=\"admin-menu-item\">GENERAL SETTINGS</span> and uncheck the <em>Page Cache</em> option, then empty the cache and re-test.</li>\n<li>WooCommerce sites using W3 Total Cache must check this:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://kb.oboxthemes.com/articles/woocommerce-order-status-not-changing-on-order-complete/\">WooCommerce: Order status not changing on order complete</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Any plugin that imports data from another site will kill performance. This includes plugins that pull in feeds from an RSS source, social network plugins that pull in status updates, Flickr plugins that auto-post photos, and so on.</li>\n<li>WooCommerce sites should have SSL enabled only for the shop pages. Do not force it on the rest of your site as it just increases the amount of checks on the server end, unless you are using Obox Social Commerce or another Facebook app that requires full domain SSL. Contact your host for help with this step if you are eunsure how to target specific parts of your site or don’t know how to wildcard urls.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Install a Caching Plugin</h3>\n<p>I know, I know, we just said you should reduce the number of plugins installed, and have pointed out some issues with some caching plugins, but the bottom line is that when configured correctly, they increase speed for subsequent visits to your site substantially and do not take much memory.</p>\n<p>If you want to forego using a plugin, check with your host on what kind of Server-side caching is available, such as Cloudflare, AWS, or Varnish</p>\n<p><strong>For advanced admins</strong> or sites that need a lot of control on Caching options, we recommend W3 Total Cache <strong>without Page Caching enabled</strong>. Please see the author’s documentation on configuration, and if you use WooCommerce, <a href=\"http://kb.oboxthemes.com/articles/woocommerce-order-status-not-changing-on-order-complete/\" target=\"_blank\">see this article!</a></p>\n<p><strong>For beginners</strong> or basic blog/portfolio sites, Quick Cache is a solid and actively developed plugin.</p>\n<p><strong>For advice and tips</strong> on which plugins are tested on Obox Themes and which our customers have used., or which plugins to watch out for, see</p>\n<p class=\"post-title\"><a title=\"Plugin Compatibility\" href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/plugin-compatibility/\" target=\"_blank\">What plugins are compatible with Layers?</a></p>\n<h3>Increase Memory</h3>\n<p>See the following for advice from WordPress on how you can attempt to increase the memory allocated to your site. Some hosts do not allow edits to the php.ini, so you may need to contact them for help and troubleshooting on this step.</p>\n<p>WordPress Codex:<a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Editing_wp-config.php#Increasing_memory_allocated_to_PHP\" target=\"_blank\"> Increasing Memory Limit</a></p>\n<h3 class=\"section-title\">Verify Server-side configurations</h3>\n<p>Things like extra content in your <strong>wp_config.php</strong> can trigger a ton of errors which you may not be seeing on the front-end, but which will slow the site.</p>\n<p>Server-side security or <strong>.htaccess</strong> problems can also cause slowdowns with WordPress trying to write <a class=\"glossaryLink\" title=\"Glossary: Permalinks\" href=\"http://kb.oboxthemes.com/glossary/permalinks/\">permalinks</a> or execute other functionality. This is typically a step you will need your host to help you troubleshoot if nothing else is helping.</p>\n<p>The following article offers some great advice for optimizing your setup, specifically when working with caching plugins like W3 Total Cache:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://blog.newrelic.com/2013/02/07/web-performance-optimization-automation/\" target=\"_blank\">Web Performance Optimizations for WordPress</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/how-to-speed-up-your-website/\">How to Speed Up Your WordPress Website</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/how-to-speed-up-your-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:8:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"The Essential Guide to WordPress Theme Customization for Beginners\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/the-essential-guide-to-wordpress-theme-customization-for-beginners/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/the-essential-guide-to-wordpress-theme-customization-for-beginners/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 10 Nov 2015 13:37:15 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"wordpress theme customization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=1787\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:623:\"<p>Even if you know enough about WordPress theme customization to be dangerous, there are probably things you\'re doing the hard way, or the wrong way. Thankfully, there are many simple things you can do to customize the look and feel of your site that don\'t require editing any files, or for you to be a professional developer.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/the-essential-guide-to-wordpress-theme-customization-for-beginners/\">The Essential Guide to WordPress Theme Customization for Beginners</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:68:\"http://docs.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/edit-widgets.mp4\";s:6:\"length\";s:6:\"981168\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"video/mp4\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Vail Joy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16321:\"<p>If you’re new to WordPress, you&#8217;ve probably arrived at that confusing question of &#8220;How can I change how my site looks?&#8221; Layers gives you a solid set of beginner tools for customizing layouts, colors and fonts, but what if you want to do something more specific, like add background texture to inside pages, or change the hover color on your nav menu?</p>\n<p>Even if you know enough about WordPress theme customization to be dangerous, there are probably things you&#8217;re doing the hard way, or the wrong way.</p>\n<p>Thankfully, there are many simple things you can do to customize the look and feel of your site that don&#8217;t require editing any files, or for you to be a professional developer.</p>\n<div style=\"width: 640px; \" class=\"wp-video\"><!--[if lt IE 9]><script>document.createElement(\'video\');</script><![endif]-->\n<video class=\"wp-video-shortcode\" id=\"video-1787-1\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" preload=\"metadata\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"video/mp4\" src=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/edit-widgets.mp4?_=1\" /><a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/edit-widgets.mp4\">http://docs.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/edit-widgets.mp4</a></video></div>\n<h3>The WordPress Customizer</h3>\n<p>WordPress is quickly moving towards a visual customization experience that is based on intuitive interfaces, direct front-end editing and layout building with widgets. By default, the WordPress Customizer offers you a preview of your website, a custom logo and favicon setting, a background color option, menu customization and a panel for your sidebar and footer widgets.</p>\n<p>With Layers activated, these options are greatly extended to include logo and menu positions, primary site colors, footer column choices, fonts and more.</p>\n<p>Layers Widgets are your building blocks for creating unique page layouts in combination with the Layers page template, or for customizing widget content look and feel in any widget area of a child theme. The Customizer allows you to see your changes on the front-end while you move things around on the back end.</p>\n<p>You can even take advantage of CSS editing directly from the customizer, which we will get to in a moment.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Appearance_Customize_Screen\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about the WordPress Customizer</a></p>\n<p><iframe width=\"660\" height=\"371\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tcC7czcawsY?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<h3>Style Kits</h3>\n<p>If you just want to change the look and feel of your Layers site, but don&#8217;t feel up to a crash course in webpage styling (CSS), Style Kits are a quick and inexpensive way to apply pre-made professional styles to your site without requiring another theme. We even use one here on our blog!</p>\n<p>To get an idea how they work, check out our little <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-create-a-style-kit/\">Style Kit guide</a> and grab the freebie kit.</p>\n<p>You can find free kits specifically made for Layers around the web or from our <a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/category/skins/layers-wp-style-kits?ref=obox\">Marketplace</a>. Compared to what it costs to hire a designer, Style Kits can save you <em>hundreds of dollars.</em></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/product/style-kits/\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about Style Kits</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/devkit-state.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1635\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/devkit-state.png\" alt=\"devkit-state\" width=\"576\" height=\"167\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/devkit-state-300x87.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/devkit-state.png 576w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Custom CSS</h3>\n<p>If you know a thing or two about styling or feel up to learning something new, CSS is the definitive method for customizing your site&#8217;s look and feel. You&#8217;ve probably seen this term used a lot in relation to web design and customization.</p>\n<p>With CSS, you can change colors, fonts, heights, padding, margins and  just about anything that does not compromise the overall structure.</p>\n<p>CSS has three main parts, the <span style=\"color: #339966;\"><strong>selector</strong></span>, the <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>property</strong></span> and the <span style=\"color: #33cccc;\"><strong>value.</strong></span> Selectors are determined by the programmer when building the framework for your site. They can be the HTML tags composing the structure of the page, or a <strong>class</strong> name added to the HTML tag.</p>\n<p>For example, the menu links in Layers are <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">a</pre>  HTML elements inside an unordered list <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">ul</pre>  with the class <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">nav-horizontal</pre> . When put together, it would look something like this if we want to change the <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">color</span> <strong>property</strong> to a <strong>value</strong> of <span style=\"color: #33cccc;\">blue</span>.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">.nav-horizontal li a{color: blue;}</pre><p>At first it may seem complicated, but CSS is the easiest web programming language to begin learning thanks to its semantic quality. Understanding the basics of CSS is an essential skill if you manage websites for yourself or others. It helps you use the huge library of customization tutorials on the internet and our very own Docs site to tweak the look of your site and save money on hiring a designer.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re wondering how you can determine what selectors to use to even begin custom styling, webkit browsers such as Chrome, Firefox and Safari  come with a wonderful inspector tool for viewing the HTML and associated CSS of anything you right-click on.</p>\n<p>Learn more about using this feature in our <a class=\"question-title\" href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-customize-your-site-with-css/\" rel=\"bookmark\">How to Customize Your Site With CSS</a> tutorial.</p>\n<p>We recommend checking out the <a href=\"https://www.codecademy.com/courses/web-beginner-en-TlhFi/0/1?curriculum_id=50579fb998b470000202dc8b\" target=\"_blank\">free CodeAcademy CSS course</a> to get a quick grip on CSS. CodeAcademy uses beginner language and an interactive format for helping you master web languages quickly.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/user/obox/portfolio?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;term=layers&amp;ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Extensions\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-303\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/envato-announcement.jpg\" alt=\"envato-announcement\" width=\"713\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/envato-announcement-300x180.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/envato-announcement.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Plugins &amp; Extensions</h3>\n<p>Just about anything you can think of needing for your website can be done with a plugin or extension, which are how WordPress adds specific functionality to your site.</p>\n<p>Plugins and extensions offer a major benefit in allowing you to pick and choose how to build your site, versus using a theme package with a ton of options and features you may not need which are overwhelming to learn how to configure.</p>\n<p>For example, if you plan to build an online store and know you want to be able to customize the shop a little, add a product tab for Wash &amp; Care instructions, and allow your users to &#8220;Quick View&#8221;the products, you can use Layers with <a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/storekit-woocommerce-for-layers/11223808?ref=obox\" target=\"_blank\">StoreKit</a>, <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-poor-guys-swiss-knife/\" target=\"_blank\">Poor Guys Swiss Knife</a> and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/yith-woocommerce-tab-manager/\" target=\"_blank\">YITH WooCommerce Tabs</a> for a grand total of $21. That is less than any premium theme and still gets you the support you need where it matters most.</p>\n<h4>What&#8217;s the Difference?</h4>\n<p>An extension differs from a plugin in that it is built for use with a specific framework like Layers or WooCommerce, whereas plugins are not dependent on what else you have installed.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/storekit/\">StoreKit</a> is an extension for Layers that adds WooCommerce customization and some product widgets you can add to your pages that come with all the cool Layers widget customizability.</p>\n<p>YITH WooCommerce Tabs is an extension for WooCommerce that obviously doesn&#8217;t provide much function if WooCommerce is not installed. Image Widget, or Yoast SEO are both essential plugins for WordPress that work with any theme and do not require other plugins to be installed.</p>\n<p>To find Layers Extensions, visit the <strong>Marketplace</strong> link in your WordPress admin panel. To find WooCommerce extensions, visit the WooCommerce website, or go to <strong>Plugins</strong> &#8211;  <strong>Add New</strong> and search for WooCommerce. This free plugin repository has a near-endless number of excellent plugins you can choose from.</p>\n<h4>How to Choose</h4>\n<p>When choosing free plugins, it is important to check out the <em>Details</em> to ensure the plugin does what you want, is user-friendly, and produces good-looking results. Each plugin has a rating, along with how many installs, and a date it was last updated. Always choose highly-rated plugins that have been updated recently or are verified compatible with your version of WordPress.</p>\n<p>With premium extensions, check what the framework author has to offer before going to independently authored extensions, to ensure the best integration and support options.</p>\n<p>A word of caution &#8211; don&#8217;t go too crazy with the free plugin installs. Not all plugins are created equal, and because they are designed by a huge variety of developers for no cost, they simply can&#8217;t guarantee cross-compatibility with your unique setup.</p>\n<p>In most cases, an actively-developed plugin with a good rating will have very few compatibility issues, but it is always a good idea to check the Support tab of the plugin&#8217;s Details page to see what kind of issues, if any, folks are reporting. <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/plugin-compatibility/\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about Layers plugin compatibility</a> over on the Layers Docs website.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://themeforest.net/user/obox/portfolio?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;term=layers?ref=obox\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-85\" src=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/coffee.jpg\" alt=\"coffee\" width=\"660\" height=\"745\" srcset=\"http://d2m1ao5c1vnep2.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/coffee-266x300.jpg 266w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/coffee.jpg 660w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Child Themes</h3>\n<p>The final and most thorough way to customize your WordPress site using Layers or any other theme, is through a child theme. A child theme is jut like any other theme except it is able to inherit all of the functionality and front-end structure from Layers (the “parent”)  while including its own special styles and functions.</p>\n<p>You can purchase professionally designed <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/attributes/framework/layers wp?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=layerswp&amp;utm_medium=cta&amp;utm_content=AllAuthors&amp;utm_campaign=Layers+Blog&amp;clickthrough_id&amp;redirect_back=true\">Child Themes</a> for Layers from the Marketplace page in your WordPress admin, or you can make your own.</p>\n<h4 class=\"section-title\">When to Use a Child Theme</h4>\n<p>The division between themes and plugins in WordPress has been a bit blurry for a long time, as both can introduce new functionality to a WordPress install, so you always want to see what can be done with all your other options first.</p>\n<p>You need a Child Theme when:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You want to re-style a theme without or beyond what the WordPress customizer controls or other plugins allow you to do,</li>\n<li>You want to add a bit of code to a specific place (such as a search field in the header) or</li>\n<li>You want to add custom page templates</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When you need to find a plugin or build an Extension:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You want to add Custom Post Types</li>\n<li>You want to add Layers Builder Widgets</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Child themes are for presentation, whereas extensions are for extending functionality.</p>\n<h3>Child Themes vs Style Kits</h3>\n<p>As you can see, there are a ton of options for customizing your site with a range of functionality requiring little skill, but two of these may sound a little similar. Both child themes and style kits involve<strong> custom css</strong> to a degree but are not the same.</p>\n<h4><strong>Style Kit</strong></h4>\n<p>Collection of presets generated from the Layers Customizer. Style Kits include the page builder widget setup, options and color settings, along with any internal assets required such as fonts or icons.</p>\n<h4><strong>Child Theme</strong></h4>\n<p>Used when a style kit is not enough and usually includes multiple stylesheets, additional scripts and a functions file defining custom Actions allow you to inject a custom function or bit of code into a specific place.</p>\n<p>You can create a custom Action using the main WordPress <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/add_action\" target=\"_blank\">Action API</a> to add or remove code from an existing core action by specifying any <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugin_API/Action_Reference\" target=\"_blank\">existing Hook</a>. Thus the term &#8220;hooking.&#8221; Layers also offers an Action API for hooking into our own custom actions.</p>\n<p><strong>For example:</strong> You may want to <strong>add</strong> code to the footer of Layers. This can be accomplished by writing new function containing your custom code, then Hooking it to the <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugin_API/Action_Reference/wp_footer\" target=\"_blank\">wp_footer</a> core action OR use the Layers Action API to take advantage of better placement.</p>\n<p>The action will output a custom element just above the copyright bar, for instance. Custom Actions differ from custom <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#Filter\" target=\"_blank\">Filters</a> because custom Actions allow you to <strong>add or remove</strong> code from existing Actions. Whereas custom Filters allow you to <strong>replace</strong> specific data (such as a variable or CSS class) found within an existing Action.</p>\n<h5><strong>From the WordPress Codex:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugin_API#Actions\" target=\"_blank\">Actions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugin_API/Action_Reference\" target=\"_blank\">Action Reference</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/add_action\" target=\"_blank\">add_action()</a> actions and filters</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Learn more about <a href=\"http://docs.layerswp.com/child-theme-author-guide/\" target=\"_blank\">making Child Themes for Layers</a></p>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>WordPress sites are incredibly flexible things, so it is no wonder it powers 25% of the internet. With a little time and planning, you can turn your Layers site into literally anything by applying one or a combination of these techniques. Keep an eye on this space as we cover specific CSS tricks and take a closer look at some of the awesome free and premium extensions and child themes to help you achieve your goals.</p>\n<p>What are some of your favorite tools for WordPress customization? Share with us below!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/the-essential-guide-to-wordpress-theme-customization-for-beginners/\">The Essential Guide to WordPress Theme Customization for Beginners</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.layerswp.com\">Layers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/the-essential-guide-to-wordpress-theme-customization-for-beginners/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:29:\"http://www.layerswp.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";a:11:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Thu, 18 Feb 2016 07:44:08 GMT\";s:6:\"server\";s:22:\"Apache/2.2.22 (Ubuntu)\";s:12:\"x-powered-by\";s:22:\"PHP/5.3.10-1ubuntu3.15\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Thu, 04 Feb 2016 14:06:26 GMT\";s:12:\"x-robots-tag\";s:15:\"noindex, follow\";s:4:\"link\";s:60:\"<http://www.layerswp.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";s:4:\"vary\";s:15:\"Acc